race.comment: BRULLEN (1) doesn't have the greatest winning strike rate - 2 from 20 - but has been beaten less than a length at his past two in much stronger races than this. The other big thing in his favour is his on-pace racing style, so the low draw suits and he might just prove too good. JESSUP (2) is a stablemate to the topweight who also draws well and shouldn't be far away. Last start was disappointing but the form previous was good enough to take this out. LADY ELSA (8) had a productive second campaign and will no doubt be better for that. While the jumpouts have suggested she'll be better for this, she looks to have upside than most rivals here. MICKIDAMUZZ (12) turned in a nice first-up run, which followed some nice jumpouts, so he could be in for a handy campaign.
